main event: Three unidentified objects were sighted over Fullerton, Nebraska on July 8, 1954.
interesting points: The objects were described as a 'bright ship with pulsating lights', a 'cup-shaped object', and a 'tube-shaped object with humps'.
The objects ranged in size from 100 feet long and were reported to be black with white borders.
The objects were sighted separately and did not appear to be in formation.
One of the cup-shaped objects appeared to have a cable sticking out of the top.
The children who witnessed the objects were described as having good eyesight and being truthful, with the investigator believing they actually saw something.
sighted object: three unidentified objects of various shapes and sizes
photographs: no photographs included in the report
